      "updated_at": "1970-01-01T00:00:00Z",
      "valid_scope": "section_pair",
      "why_conflicting": "Authentication specifies a 48-hour inactivity timeout for sessions, while Session Termination specifies a 24-hour inactivity window after which sessions are purged. These two values directly contradict each other for the same concept (session inactivity expiry), creating an ambiguous contract for implementors and auditors.",
      "why_llm_cannot_decide": "Both values (48 hours and 24 hours) appear as authoritative specifications within the same document. Neither the shared Purpose (smoke-check fixture for spec-anchor CLI) nor the Core Concept (minimal sample designed not to fire LLM conflicts) clarifies which timeout is canonical. The Core Concept explicitly states the sample is designed to avoid LLM-detected conflicts, yet this numerical discrepancy is a real contradiction that cannot be resolved without a human authorship decision on the intended inactivity threshold."
    }
  ],
